    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-11-30T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-11-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="384"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <head>384. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Jordan</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d384fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 785.00/11–3058. Secret; Priority; Limited Distribution. Repeated to
                        Cairo, Damascus, and <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Amman</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-11-30T22:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1958—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1442. Early this evening Palace protocol officer called said King Hussein wished
                    see me. On arrival Palace I was surprised find King alone (usually he has Rifai
                    with him).</p>
                <p>He opened conversation by saying he had not seen me for several days and while he
                    had no urgent problems, did wish discuss some matters general interest. He began
                    by asking my opinion on decision lift martial law which he said was designed
                    first counter influence foreign press which had labeled Jordan police state,
                    second, serve as answer <persName corresp="#p_NGA1">Nasser</persName>’s latest
                    propaganda attack which inferred Hussein afraid his own people. I replied on
                    basis my conversation early today with Prime Minister Rifai it would appear
                    so-called lifting martial law was for purely psychological reasons, from
                    practical standpoint would be little change present conditions. King admitted
                    this, but said he hoped over period months army could be relieved its police
                    duties which are destroying its effectiveness both as fighting force and as
                    special instrument suppress public demonstrations when situation gets beyond
                    control civil authorities.</p>
                <pb facs="0699" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/>
                <p>King launched into bitter attack on <persName corresp="#p_NGA1">Nasser</persName>
                    for his latest insults, said he has about reached limit his patience. He would
                    like counter propaganda offensive but Prime Minister Rifai takes position
                        <persName corresp="#p_NGA1">Nasser</persName> has violated <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> resolution therefore it is <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> Ambassador <persName>Spinelli</persName>’s responsibility deal
                    with matter. Hussein is convinced neither <persName>Spinelli</persName> or
                        <gloss target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> can handle <persName
                        corresp="#p_NGA1">Nasser</persName> even if they wanted to which he doubts.
                    He said <persName>Spinelli</persName>’s record to date most disappointing
                    pointed out not a single Jordanian oil truck has been permitted transit Syria
                    while charges on phosphate trucks have been raised to point margin profit
                    completely wiped out. Although <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> resolution
                    passed August 21 it is now December, yet neither <persName>Spinelli</persName>
                    nor any member his organization has even visited Damascus where <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> was supposed to open office. [<hi rend="italic">3
                        lines of source text not declassified</hi>]</p>
                <p>King expressed his appreciation delivery Hawker Hunter aircraft, was pleased to
                    hear spare parts should begin arriving December 9.</p>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">2 paragraphs (1½ pages of source text) not
                    declassified</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WTK1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Wright</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
